eng-ssh(7)

# NAME

eng-ssh - SSH agent architecture and configuration

# DESCRIPTION

The *eng* environment uses a three-layer SSH agent stack that combines
hardware-backed PIV keys with software certificates (e.g. Step CA). An
agent multiplexer presents a single socket to SSH clients.

# AGENT STACK

Three agent sockets live under _~/.local/state/ssh/_:

*pivy-agent.sock*
	PIV hardware key agent. Exposes YubiKey slots 9A and 9D. Launchd service *net.cooperi.pivy-agent* (see _home/pivy-agent.nix_).

*launchd-agent.sock*
	Symlink to macOS built-in ssh-agent. Holds software-added keys (Step SSH certificates). Created by fish interactiveShellInit (see _home/fish.nix_).

*mux-agent.sock*
	ssh-agent-mux multiplexer combining both upstream agents. Config at _~/.config/ssh-agent-mux/ssh-agent-mux.toml_ (see _home/ssh-agent-mux.nix_).

The multiplexer config routes *add_identity* requests to the launchd
agent (via *add-new-keys-to = "launchd"*), so Step certificates and
other software keys land there, not in pivy-agent.

# AUTHENTICATION FLOW

When SSH connects to a host:

. SSH reads IdentityAgent from the matching host config to determine which agent socket to query.
. The agent lists available identities from its upstream sources.
. SSH tries each identity until the server accepts one.
. The agent routes the signing request to whichever upstream agent owns the accepted key.

For hosts using *mux-agent.sock*, both PIV keys and Step certificates
are available. For hosts that explicitly set *IdentityAgent* to a
specific socket (e.g. _launchd-agent.sock_ or _1password-agent.sock_),
only that agent's keys are tried.

# SSH CONFIG CHAIN

The SSH config is generated by home-manager (_home/ssh.nix_) and
extended by rcm-deployed includes:

. _~/.config/ssh/config_ — entry point (home-manager generated).
. _~/.config/ssh/rcm/config-client_ — ForwardAgent, ControlMaster, ControlPersist.
. _~/.config/ssh/rcm/config-user_ — personal host definitions (github-user).
. _~/.config/ssh/config-local_ — per-machine overrides (includes child repo configs).
. _~/.config/ssh/rcm/config-user-secret_ — private host definitions.

Child repositories add their own SSH config fragments. See
*eng-etsy-step*(7) for the Etsy Step CA integration.

# AGENT FORWARDING

The *config-client* sets *ForwardAgent* to the mux-agent socket path.
This means remote hosts receive an agent that can sign with both PIV
keys and Step certificates. Individual host blocks can override this
with *ForwardAgent yes* (forward) or *ForwardAgent no* (block).

# KNOWN HOSTS

Two known_hosts files are configured via *UserKnownHostsFile*:

- _~/.config/ssh/rcm/known_hosts_ — shared known hosts (rcm-deployed)
- _~/.config/ssh/rcm/known_hosts-user_ — user-specific additions

# TROUBLESHOOTING

*Agent has no identities*
	Run *ssh -v host* and check the IdentityAgent line, then test: *env SSH_AUTH_SOCK=<socket> ssh-add -l*.

*pivy-agent has no identities*
	YubiKey may need unlocking. Run *pivy-tool list* to verify, then *ssh-add -l* via pivy-agent.sock.

*launchd-agent.sock missing or stale*
	Created by fish interactive init. Open a new terminal, or: *ln -sf $(launchctl getenv SSH_AUTH_SOCK) ~/.local/state/ssh/launchd-agent.sock*.

*mux-agent not combining both agents*
	Check _~/.local/state/ssh-agent-mux/ssh-agent-mux.log_. Ensure both upstream sockets exist.

# FILES

_~/.local/state/ssh/pivy-agent.sock_
	PIV agent socket.

_~/.local/state/ssh/launchd-agent.sock_
	Symlink to macOS launchd ssh-agent.

_~/.local/state/ssh/mux-agent.sock_
	Agent multiplexer socket.

_~/.config/ssh-agent-mux/ssh-agent-mux.toml_
	Multiplexer configuration.

_~/.config/ssh/config_
	SSH client configuration (home-manager generated).

# SEE ALSO

*eng*(7), *eng-etsy-step*(7), *pivy-agent*(1), *ssh-agent-mux*(1),
*ssh_config*(5)
